value.name: Job Search - Query
value.description: Returns job postings. Supports keyword/location search and paging via query string parameters.

queryParameters.name: limit
queryParameters.description: The number of jobs to return. Defaults to the maximum (100) if no value is specified.

queryParameters.name: offset
queryParameters.description: The number of jobs to skip before returning results. Defaults to zero if no value is specified.

queryParameters.name: sort
queryParameters.description: The field name on which to sort. Defaults to modifyDate if not specified.

queryParameters.name: order
queryParameters.description: The direction of the sort. Defaults to descending if not specified

queryParameters.name: keyword
queryParameters.description: The keyword(s) on which to base the job search.

queryParameters.name: location
queryParameters.description: A geographic location on which to base the job search.

queryParameters.name: datepublished
queryParameters.description: Filters the jobs based on when they were posted.

queryParameters.name: companyname
queryParameters.description: The company associated with the job.

queryParameters.name: city
queryParameters.description: The city in which the job exists.

queryParameters.name: province
queryParameters.description: The state in which the job exists.

queryParameters.name: includeskillshistogram
queryParameters.description: Flag to include a histogram of skills related with the job search results

queryParameters.name: country
queryParameters.description: Country code

queryParameters.name: industry
queryParameters.description: Industry name

queryParameters.name: jobcategory
queryParameters.description: Job category name

queryParameters.name: postalcode
queryParameters.description: Postal code

queryParameters.name: streetaddress
queryParameters.description: Street address

queryParameters.name: employmenttype
queryParameters.description: Employment type (valid values are: "Full-Time", "Part-Time", "Contractor", "Temporary", "Other")

queryParameters.name: experiencelevel
queryParameters.description: Experience level

queryParameters.name: educationlevel
queryParameters.description: Education level

queryParameters.name: searchradius
queryParameters.description: Search radius in miles

responses.description: Returns active jobs that conform to the query parameters.

value.name: Job Alert - Create
value.description: Creates a job alert for the job and subscriber defined by the url template parameters. A subscriber may only have five active job alerts at any given time. Note that the dates and times are UTC (it is the responsibility of the calling code to convert to the user's local time zone).

request.description: The job alert to be created. Note that the dates and times are UTC (it is the responsibility of the calling code to convert to the user's local time zone). Only two values may be passed to "frequency": "Weekly" or "Daily". Weekly alerts require the "executionDayOfWeek" parameter to be populated - acceptable values for this field are "Sunday", "Monday", "Tuesday", "Wednesday", "Thursday", and "Saturday". For Daily alerts, the "executionDayOfWeek" parameter is ignored.

            "targetProperty": "JobDescription",
            "parsedValue": "A servant-leader responsible for managing, motivating and developing self-organizing agile teams and aligning their efforts with the purpose and goals of the company. Essential functions include:- Manage multiple teams of approximately 30 people comprised of internal employees as well as onshore and offshore contractors.- Lead the recruitment and hiring of new Team-members (with the active involvement and input of the existing Team-members).- Provide input to the Product Owner on the product strategy and vision, and give feedback to the Product Owner on the content and prioritization of the Product Backlog.- Provide support and assistance to Team and Scrum Masters by proactively helping to remove impediments that are harming Teams' ability to be effective.- Provide mentorship, career development advice and guidance, and complete performance evaluations for Team-members.- Remove Team-members that are not able to perform well within a given Team, work effectively with their fellow Team-members, or perform work at the level of expertise or quality required.- Perform financial planning and budgeting for Teams, including anticipating future people requirements, skills development and training needs and any other resources that people will require.",

value.name: Subscriber Profile Resume Parse

value.name: Subscriber Profile Resume Questions - Update
value.description: Endpoint for supply answers to resume merge questions

request.description: To construct the payload, call Subscriber Profile Resume Questions (GET). There are two types of questions: Radio buttons (rb) and Checkboxes (chk). Under each resumeParse property, take the resumeParseResultGuid and append 'rb_' or chk_' based on type of the question followed by a semicolon. The possible answer is 'existing','parsed','neither'.

value.description: Each request will the user's avatar

value.name: Job Alert - Edit

templateParameters.name: jobAlert
templateParameters.description: This is a unique identifier for a job alert

value.description: Updates a job alert for the job and subscriber defined by the url template parameters. A subscriber may only have five active job alerts at any given time. Note that the dates and times are UTC (it is the responsibility of the calling code to convert to the user's local time zone).

request.description: The job alert to be created. Note that the dates and times are UTC (it is the responsibility of the calling code to convert to the user's local time zone). Only two values may be passed to "frequency": "Weekly" or "Daily". Weekly alerts require the "executionDayOfWeek" parameter to be populated - acceptable values for this field are "Sunday", "Monday", "Tuesday", "Wednesday", "Thursday", and "Saturday". For Daily alerts, the "executionDayOfWeek" parameter is ignored.

value.description: Returns talent based on search criteria

queryParameters.name: limit
queryParameters.description: The number of jobs to return. Defaults to the maximum (100) if no value is specified.

queryParameters.name: offset
queryParameters.description: The number of jobs to skip before returning results. Defaults to zero if no value is specified.

queryParameters.name: orderBy
queryParameters.description: The order of the search results.  Only values from "Talent Search - Order By" can be used

queryParameters.name: keyword
queryParameters.description: The keyword(s) on which to base the talent search.

queryParameters.name: location
queryParameters.description: A geographic location on which to base the talent search.

queryParameters.name: partner
queryParameters.description: Partner that subscriber is associated with

responses.description: Returns active jobs that conform to the query parameters.

responses.description: Expired jobs will return a 410 status but will still contain the job detail (which can be used for similar job queries).

workHistoryQuestions.parsedValue: A servant-leader responsible for managing, motivating and developing self-organizing agile teams and aligning their efforts with the purpose and goals of the company. Essential functions include:- Manage multiple teams of approximately 30 people comprised of internal employees as well as onshore and offshore contractors.- Lead the recruitment and hiring of new Team-members (with the active involvement and input of the existing Team-members).- Provide input to the Product Owner on the product strategy and vision, and give feedback to the Product Owner on the content and prioritization of the Product Backlog.- Provide support and assistance to Team and Scrum Masters by proactively helping to remove impediments that are harming Teams' ability to be effective.- Provide mentorship, career development advice and guidance, and complete performance evaluations for Team-members.- Remove Team-members that are not able to perform well within a given Team, work effectively with their fellow Team-members, or perform work at the level of expertise or quality required.- Perform financial planning and budgeting for Teams, including anticipating future people requirements, skills development and training needs and any other resources that people will require.

workHistory.title: Technical Team Lead
workHistory.jobDescription: I was hired to enhance and maintain the lead workflow system thatsupports our agency clients in a variety of industries (education,mortgage, insurance, and health services). In January 2014, I waspromoted to technical lead for this team.●  The primary lead workflow system processes tens of thousands of transactions per day from hundreds of 3rd party vendors. The primaryservice receives a message, processes business rules using a ruleengine, routes the message based on the result of those rules, and provides status information in the web response to the subscriber of the service in just a few seconds. All of this is done while relying on 3rdparty services for some of the business rules which increases theoverall lead processing time - were it not for those 3rd party services,we could process the lead in under a second every time. Thecomplexity of this system has grown since I began however the performance has not degraded.●  While the majority of my dev time has been spent working on webservices, database code, and BizTalk to support the system I describedpreviously, I have also spent a considerable amount of time building and maintaining the tools that allow the business to manage leaddelivery. This involves building reports via SSRS, creating SSISpackages for ETL and data warehousing processes, and adding newfunctionality to both a public-facing and internal web portal that can beused to modify how the primary lead delivery system functions. Thoseweb portals are built with a variety of Microsoft technologies: ASP.NETWebForms, ASP.NET MVC, Telerik UI components (for both WebForms and MVC), Entity Framework, Enterprise Library, and LINQ.●  Due to the small size of the company, individuals take on multiple roleswhich are often segregated in larger organizations. My coreresponsibilities in this role include: business analysis, software design,project planning, software development / code reviews / deployment / maintenance, and managerial responsibilities for developers thatreport to me.

workHistory.title: Senior .NET Developer

Whilethe demographics of the group had changed over the years, my focushad always been on delivering quality in a very short period of time while still maintaining best practices (search engine optimization, codescalability, standards, and reliability).●  I was the lead developer on one of our operating companies intranetsite redesigns.
